    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Red State or Blue? A Family Affair</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sam Goffman letter contends Bush administration is continuing toward disaster in variety of areas (Nov 28 Maureen Dowd Op-Ed column)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What really gets the liberal goat is what Maureen Dowd's brother Kevin ignores in his e-mail (at least the portions excerpted): the damage to the environment, needless tax cuts for the rich, the shunning of the rest of the world, the lies and hypocrisy behind the war in Iraq.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What really gets the liberal goat is what Maureen Dowd's brother Kevin ignores in his e-mail (at least the portions excerpted): the damage to the environment, needless tax cuts for the rich, the shunning of the rest of the world, the lies and hypocrisy behind the war in Iraq.</p>
        <p>Behind the facade of compassion and social values, the Bush administration continues inexorably toward disaster in realms far more pressing than whether a 10th grader should learn how to have safe sex.</p>
        <p>Sam Goffman  Montreal, Nov. 28, 2004</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
